name: Gray Camry
description:
Introduction

Relatively decent canyon in the San Gabriels. completely dry (maybe in rainy season?). Nice canopy throughout. I think. I only did it an night. Only know the details of the lower half as I came up canyon and got stuck by the second 50' waterwall and could not find a way around it. Above looks scramble-able. Two 50' waterfalls (without water) a shorter 20' that's probably down-climbable and a couple more short rappels that could be down climbed. Probably lots of PO judging from the area. I'll tell you in a couple days.

As of this writing, there is a gray camry about half way down.

Approach

Park at newman's point and walk to the canyon

Descent

Exit

cross San Gabriel dam, then hike up to the HWY 39.

Red tape

This canyon ends on LA County Flood control property and they don't like visitors.
